==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''apponere'' to put near
===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# In [[grammar]], a [[construction]] in which one [[noun]] or [[noun phrase]] is placed with [[another]] as an [[expain|explanatory]] [[equivalent]], [[both]] having the same [[syntactic]] [[function]] in the [[sentence]].
# The [[relationship]] [[between]] such nouns or noun phrases.
# The quality of being side-by-side, apposed instead of being opposed, not being front-to-front but face-to-face.
# A [[placing]] of two things side by side, or the fitting together of two things.
# In [[Biology]], the [[growth]] of [[successive]] [[layer]]s of a [[cell]] [[wall]].

